    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hand-held tools, typically made of bone, ivory, steel, or wood, used to weave and repair mesh nets. Though these tools vary in appearance, they often include a smooth, well-rounded stick with a uniform thickness throughout its length. This allows for equally-sized loops to be knotted around the stick in the production of mesh. The size of the tool determines the size of mesh materials produced.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
